CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Common Ownership Communities – Ombudsman Unit Oversight, Governing
3 Document Database, and Local Commissions
4 FOR the purpose of establishing the Common Ownership Community Ombudsman Unit
5 Oversight Division in the Division of Consumer Protection in the Office of the
6 Attorney General Department of Housing and Community Development to receive
7 and respond to certain complaints; requiring common ownership communities to file
8 certain documents with the Department of Housing and Community Development;
9 requiring the Department to establish a certain database; establishing requirements
10 for a local common ownership commission established by the local government of a
11 county; and generally relating to common ownership communities.
